@startuml
participant "OZO Client" as RPA
participant "FHIR API" as FHIR
participant "OZO Platform" as CTA

== Thread Creation ==
RPA -> FHIR : Create CommunicationRequest\n(status: 'draft')\n[As RelatedPerson]
FHIR -> FHIR : Create Tasks\nfor each CareTeam member\n(status: 'requested')
FHIR -> CTA : Notify of new CommunicationRequest\n[Via Subscription]
CTA -> FHIR : Fetch CommunicationRequest
CTA -> FHIR : Update CommunicationRequest\n(status: 'active')\n[After approval]
FHIR -> RPA : Notify of updated CommunicationRequest\n[Via Subscription]

== Practitioner Responds ==
CTA -> FHIR : Create Communication\n[Practitioner -> RelatedPerson]
FHIR -> FHIR : Update Tasks\n(status: 'requested' for recipients)
FHIR -> RPA : Notify of new Communication\n[Via Subscription]
note over RPA : New message detected\nvia Communication subscription\n(not via Task)
RPA -> FHIR : Fetch Communication

== Caregiver Reads Message ==
RPA -> FHIR : Create AuditEvent\n(action: 'R', agent: RelatedPerson)
FHIR -> FHIR : Update Task\n(status: 'completed')\nfor RelatedPerson
FHIR -> CTA : Notify of Task update\n[Via Subscription]
note over CTA : Message marked as read\nby RelatedPerson

== Caregiver Responds ==
RPA -> FHIR : Create Communication\n[RelatedPerson -> CareTeam]
FHIR -> FHIR : Update Tasks\n(status: 'requested' for CareTeam members)
FHIR -> CTA : Notify of new Communication\n[Via Subscription]
note over CTA : New message detected\nvia Communication subscription
CTA -> FHIR : Fetch Communication
note over CTA : When one practitioner reads,\nmarked as read for all CareTeam members

== Thread Completion ==
RPA -> FHIR : Update CommunicationRequest\n(status: 'completed')
@enduml
